  "Allegations" : "SEC LITIGATION RELEASE 21924, APRIL 8, 2011: THE UNITED STATES SECURITIES AND EXCHANGE COMMISSION (\"COMMISSION\") FILED A CIVIL ACTION AGAINST PAUL N. NICHOLSON AND HIS FORMER FIRM ALLEGING THAT THEY DIRECTED TWO FRAUDULENT OIL-AND-GAS OFFERINGS.  THE COMMISSION ALLEGED THAT NICHOLSON VIOLATED SECTIONS 5(A), 5(C), AND 17(A) OF THE SECURITIES ACT OF 1933 (\"SECURITIES ACT\") AND SECTIONS 10(B) AND 15(A) OF THE SECURITIES EXCHANGE ACT OF 1934 (\"EXCHANGE ACT\") AND RULE 10B-5 THEREUNDER.  THE COMMISSION ALLEGED THAT FROM MAY 2007 THROUGH OCTOBER 2009, NICHOLSON AND HIS MANAGING GENERAL PARTNER FIRM FRAUDULENTLY RAISED APPROXIMATELY $8.2 MILLION FROM INVESTORS THROUGH TWO LIMITED PARTNERSHIPS.  THE COMMISSION ALLEGED THAT, IN PARTICULAR, THAT NICHOLSON, WHO ALSO FORMERLY OPERATED A BROKER-DEALER, AND THE MANAGING GENERAL PARTNER ENTITY HE CONTROLLED, MISUSED AND MISAPPROPRIATED INVESTOR FUNDS, INCLUDING, AMONG OTHER THINGS, USING INVESTOR FUNDS TO PAY UNDISCLOSED COMMISSIONS TO UNLICENSED SALESPEOPLE, TO PAY THE BROKER-DEALER'S EXPENSES AND TO PAY UNDISCLOSED PERSONAL SALARY AND EXPENSES.  THE COMMISSION ALSO ALLEGED THAT IN COMMUNICATIONS WITH POTENTIAL AND EXISTING INVESTORS, NICHOLSON ENGAGED IN CONDUCT THAT OPERATED AS A FRAUD AND DECEIT ON INVESTORS, INCLUDING BY OMITTING MATERIAL INFORMATION ABOUT THE USE OF INVESTOR PROCEEDS AND ABOUT THE PAST PERFORMANCE OF NICHOLSON'S AND THE MANAGING GENERAL PARTNER ENTITY'S OIL-AND-GAS VENTURES.  THE COMMISSION FURTHER ALLEGED THAT NICHOLSON SOLD UNREGISTERED SECURITIES AND THAT HE OPERATED THE MANAGING GENERAL PARTNER ENTITY AS AN UNREGISTERED BROKER-DEALER.  IN EARLY 2010, NICHOLSON TRANSFERRED CONTROL OF THE MANAGING GENERAL PARTNER ENTITY TO NEW MANAGEMENT AND DEREGISTERED HIS BROKER-DEALER.",
